Police made arrests during a public auction at the Agricultural Fund building, in Pilsen
The anti-corruption police made several arrests at the Agricultural Fund building in recent days.
Detectives handcuffed a local businessman from the media sector and real estate businessman Luboš G.
Apparently, he tried to manipulate an ongoing public auction for the restitution of the rights in such a way that the auctioned land would be received by a specific interested party.
He had to pay Luboš G. half a million crowns for this.
&quot;At the moment I can only say that the police are looking for a person for bribery during a public auction and public bidding,&quot; Pilsen chief prosecutor general Antonie Zelená told Právo, adding that at the moment she cannot divulge more details about the ongoing investigation.
After 24 hours, the police released the 46-year-old businessman.
As to the way in which it could have influenced the public auction, given the little official information, one can only speculate.
Agricultural Fund spokeswoman Lubomíra Černá responded to Právo&#39;s questions by saying that the police actually carried out the arrest at the Pilsen headquarters and it was during a public auction.
&quot;This is a client, not one of our workers,&quot; he said.
According to Černá, the public auction is called &quot;Call for the submission of land transfer proposals in accordance with the law on land&quot; and is held when various interested parties appear in relation to the offered land.
&quot;These people, during the call, offer a value higher than their restitution, which must be transferred before the value of the land is announced.&quot;
&quot;Based on the offers, the order of the buyers is determined and, later, the Agricultural Fund transfers the land to the person who offers the highest offer,&quot; explained the Fund&#39;s spokesperson.
Luboš G. had information about who was going to submit to the call and, since he is also an interested person because he acquired various restitution rights, he proposed to those interested in the land that he would not participate in the auction.
