President Barack Obama today joined the national mobilization in support of the Dream Act, to legalize undocumented students, with a message on his personal account on the social network Twitter.
&quot;If you agree that passing the Dream Act is the right thing to do, call your senators and urge them to pass this legislation,&quot; Obama tweeted.
His short message holds open a web link to a larger document asking the public to contact senators immediately as a vote on the legislation is imminent.
&quot;With a vote expected to happen soon, now is the time to make your voice heard,&quot; he says.
